* {{WP|Michael Douglas}} as [[Henry Pym (Earth-199999)|Ant-Man / Dr. Hank Pym]],<ref name="Douglas announcement">{{cite web|url=http://marvel.com/news/movies/2014/1/13/21746/michael_douglas_to_star_as_hank_pym_in_marvels_ant-man|title=Michael Douglas to Star as Hank Pym in Marvel's Ant-Man|work=Marvel.com|last=|first=|date=13 January 2014|accessdate=13 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/02/15/ant-man-hank-pym-costume-revealed-sort-of|title=Ant-Man Hank Pym Costume Revealed (Sort Of)|author=Yehl, Joshua and Scott Collura|work=IGN|date=14 February 2015|accessdate=14 February 2015}}</ref> the founder of Pym Technology, inventor of the Ant-Man suit, discoverer of the Pym Particles, and the original Ant-Man. Dr. Pym distrusts super heroes due to something that happened to his late wife, Janet van Dyne, in the 1980s.<ref name="set visit"/>
** {{WP|Dax Griffin}} as young Hank Pym

Additionally, {{WP|John Slattery}} reprises his role as [[Howard Stark (Earth-199999)|Howard Stark]].<ref name="Production Starts"/> {{WP|Gregg Turkington}} appears as Dale,<ref name="Premiere"/> the manager of a Baskin-Robbins.<ref name="set visit"/><ref name="Production Starts"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2014/07/david-dastmalchian-signs-on-to-ant-man-david-harbour-to-play-corrupt-fed-in-black-mass/|title=David Dastmalchian Joins 'Ant-Man', David Harbour Adds To 'Black Mass'; 'Ride Along 2' Taps Olivia Munn|author=The Deadline Team|work=Deadline|date=2 July 2014|accessdate=1 July 2014}}</ref> Hayley Lovitt appears as [[Janet Van Dyne (Earth-199999)|Wasp / Janet van Dyne]] in a non-speaking role. [[Stan Lee]] makes a cameo appearance as a bartender.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://screenrant.com/stan-lee-avengers-age-of-ultron-cameos-gillette-giveaway/|title=Stan Lee On Upcoming Marvel Cameos & Our 'Avengers : Age of Ultron' Giveaway|last=Keyes|first=Rob|work=Screen Rant|date=30 April 2015|accessdate=23 June 2015}}</ref>  Original ''{{WP|Saturday Night Live}}'' cast member {{WP|Garrett Morris}} makes a cameo as a cab driver. Comedian {{WP|Tom Kenny}} provides his voice for a stuffed rabbit that Scott gives Cassie for her birthday. YouTube star {{WP|Anna Akana}} makes a cameo as a writer who knows the Falcon. {{WP|Chris Evans (actor)|Chris Evans}} and {{WP|Sebastian Stan}} reprise their roles as [[Steven Rogers (Earth-199999)|Steve Rogers]] and [[James Barnes (Earth-199999)|Bucky Barnes]], respectively, in a clip from ''[[Captain America: Civil War]]'' that serves as a post-credits scene.

{{WP|Jordi Mollà}} shot a scene as Castillo, a Panamanian general Hank steals a microfilm from in the 1980's, but the scene was ultimately cut from the movie.<ref name="Synopsis Dec 14"/><ref name="Trivia">{{cite web|url=http://www.comingsoon.net/movies/features/445419-ant-man-trivia-and-fun-facts#/slide/1|title=Ant-Man Trivia and Fun Facts|last=Marnell|first=Blair|work=Coming Soon|date=31 May 2015|accessdate=15 September 2015}}</ref> {{WP|Patrick Wilson (actor)|Patrick Wilson}}, {{WP|Matt Gerald}}, and {{WP|Kevin Weisman}} were cast in undisclosed roles before departing the project in July 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2014/02/patrick-wilson-to-join-marvels-ant-man/|title=Patrick Wilson To Join Marvel's 'Ant-Man'|last=Fleming Jr.|first=Mike|work=Deadline|date=27 February 2014|accessdate=1 March 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2014/04/ant-man-matt-gerald-kenneth-choi-the-whole-truth/|title=Matt Gerald Lands Villainous 'Ant-Man Role; Kenneth Choi In Court For 'The Whole Truth'|work=Deadline|date=April 2014|accessdate=5 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2014/07/comic-con-major-cast-exits-on-ant-man-include-patrick-wilson/|title=Comic-Con: Major Cast Exits on 'Ant-Man' Include Patrick Wilson|last=Yamato|first=Jen|work=Deadline|date=25 July 2014|accessdate=25 July 2014}}</ref> Wilson's role was later revealed to be that of Jim Paxton, which ultimately went to Bobby Cannavale.<ref name="Trivia"/> {{WP|Jordan Peele}} was also cast in the film, but had to leave due to scheduling conflicts at an unknown time.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/ricky-gervais-jordan-peele-tvs-801472|title=Ricky Gervais, Jordan Peele and TV's Funniest Actors on Failed Fart Skits, Louis C.K. Worship and When to Play the Race Card|last=Hunt|first=Stacy Wilson|work=17 June 2015|accessdate=15 September 2015}}</ref>

| Notes                   = 
[[File:Ant-Man Movie.jpg|right|thumb]]
* {{WP|Edgar Wright}} was the original director the film, but he exited the project in late May 2014 "due to differences in [Marvel Studios' and his] vision of the film."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thewrap.com/edgar-wright-exits-marvels-ant-man/|title=Edgar Wright Exits Marvel's 'Ant-Man'|date=23 May 2014|accessdate=23 May 2014|last=Zakarin|first=Jordan|work=The Wrap}}</ref> Directors Marvel considered to replace Wright included {{WP|Adam McKay}}, {{WP|Rawson Marshall Thurber}}, and {{WP|Ruben Fleischer}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/ant-man-director-contenders-include-707976|title='Ant-Man' Director Contenders Include Adam McKay, Ruben Fleischer|last=Siegel|first=Tatiana|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=30 May 2014|acessdate=7 June 2014}}</ref> {{WP|Peyton Reed}} officially boarded the project as its new director two weeks after Wright left, while McKay joined the project as a writer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://marvel.com/news/movies/2014/6/7/22643/director_peyton_reed_and_writer_adam_mckay_join_marvels_ant-man|title=Director Peyton Reed and writer Adam McKay join Marvel's Ant-Man|work=Marvel.com|date=7 June 2014|accessdate=7 June 2014}}</ref>
* The film wrapped principal photography on December 6, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MrPeytonReed/status/541026417203757056|title=And that's it! Principal photography on ANT-MAN is now complete. The ants have left the building. Stay tuned...|last=Reed|first=Peyton|work=Twitter|date=6 December 2014|accessdate=8 December 2014}}</ref>

| Trivia                  = * The film was originally scheduled for a November 6, 2015 release, was later moved up to July 31, 2015, and then to July 17 of the same year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.superherohype.com/news/articles/173197-ant-man-gets-a-release-date|title=Ant-Man Gets a Release Date!|date=15 October 2012|accessdate=15 October 2012|last=Perry|first=Spencer|work=SuperHeroHype!}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.comingsoon.net/news/movienews.php?id=108737|title=Ant-Man Moves Up to Summer 2015!|date=9 September 2013|accessdate=9 September 2013|work=ComingSoon.net}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://marvel.com/news/movies/2014/1/23/21811/marvels_ant-man_leaps_forward_to_july_17|title=Marvel's Ant-Man Leaps Forward to July 17|date=23 January 2014|accessdate=23 January 2014|last=Strom|first=Marc|work=Marvel.com}}</ref>
* Darren Cross refers to Pym's archived adventures as Ant-Man as "tales to astonish," a reference to the [[Tales to Astonish Vol 1|comic book series]] that introduced [[Henry Pym (Earth-616)|Hank Pym]].{{r|Tales to Astonish Vol 1 27}}
* Original ''{{WP|Saturday Night Live}}'' cast member {{WP|Garrett Morris}} makes a cameo in the film as a cab driver. Morris portrayed Ant-Man in the classic ''SNL'' sketch [http://www.hulu.com/watch/4137 "Superhero Party."]
* The filmmakers originally wanted for Scott Lang to work at {{WP|Chipotle Mexican Grill|Chipotle}}, but the restaurant chain didn't particularly like the context in which their brand would've been used. Before landing on {{WP|Baskin-Robbins}}, {{WP|Jamba Juice}} was considered.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainthis.usatoday.com/2015/07/17/ant-man-baskin-robbins/|title=Here's why Ant-Man works at Baskin-Robbins|work=USA Today|fist=Carly|last=Mallenbaum|date=17 July 2015|accessdate=24 November 2015}}</ref>
